The new terminal at the Murtala Muhammed International Airport (MMIA), Lagos, will be ready for use in February.
 
The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN), yesterday, disclosed the new completion date to House of Representatives members on an oversight function in Lagos.  “Last year, there was no apron like this, but this year, we now have it. It goes to show that FAAN is working and moving forward. We are happy with FAAN and we are ready to support the industry to move forward.” To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .